				<td colspan="2"><span>i don't understand though, you are saying that none of you other bards value CHA and DEX as top priorities? Or i am overestimating their effect on songs and landing their effects? 
<br />
I think overall i could deal with missing song notes (just a minor annoyance, hit the song key again if you miss a note), BUT my play style as a bard is quite the 'enchanter-type-bard' as in i mezz and charm alot. 
<br />
It is true that charisma affects if mezzes and charms get resisted right? If so then yes that should be a priority, if not, and it's just like dex in that it only prevents missing notes, then i could leave that out..hmm...
<br />
In this case, would AC (5) HP (1) CHA (5) or AC (1) STA (1) CHA (1) be the best choice? It will be a while before i start using songs (and the AA) that uses mana, so i'm not too concerned about that. These priorities are primarily for lvls 12-60<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
