				<td colspan="2"><span>In my experience, no matter what kind of bard you claim to be, a bard is always filling rolls.  you may be puller but you will CC some till the chanter gets ahold of it, or you may be a filler dps and suport type atm but ent up temp tanking when the MT goes down.  So while i concentrated on ac and hps, i also raised my cha and int, along with dex and agi (str is easy to get).  so since a bard is the most versitile class, carry some extra gear items for when you need it, and keep you stats somewhat level.  a 305 sta bard wont do very well CCing with 75 cha, but 200 to all stats and your fine.  and when your starting out, unless you twink your gonna be weak, so what, it build character and teaches you what being a bard is about...using your head and songs</span></td>
