				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 3 stats (and values) for bards on allakhazam.com<a name="41697"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 24 04 10:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>IMHO
<br />
Early levels - AC, STA, HP, DEX
<br />
Mid Levels  - AC, STA, CHR, INT, DEX (solo charm kites)
<br />
Upper Levels - AC, STA, CHR, INT, DEX (sets you up for fade, lull, and pulling. At this point you normally have access to great buffs for HP and other Stats)
<br />

<br />
I would say the ones that are hard to modify are INT, DEX, CHR because you're always competeing with a caster or monk for them. But they are very important to a bard. 
<br />

<br />
INT for Mana for either Fade or Charm
<br />
DEX and CHR for missed notes and success of Lull / Charm
<br />

<br />
AC is always important as I always get whacked once or twice on a pull. Once you can afford the AAs LR and ID are great to have.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
