				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 3 stats (and values) for bards on allakhazam.com<a name="42036"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 25 04 10:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Why is dex even listed?  Just doing decent gear your dex mod will be about 75% or higher of what your strength mod is.  If your dex gets to be about 180 or so you will max it with buffs (chanter or shammy).  
<br />

<br />
Cha on the other had can be hard to find depending on what you are looking for.  I would recomend about a 210-220 Cha by the time you are 65, and have the hps/AA's to be pulling hard ldon's.  Lull is kinda reliable at this point and much more when you hit 270 with buffs.   
<br />

<br />
Int can be hard to find on gear also.  And more mana is always good.  
<br />

<br />
Pretty much only sta worry about are in order for augs are Sta, Int, Cha, Agi.  But compare pure hp gear to sta gear to see what the biggest effect is.  Also if you are grouped with a shammy 90% of the time consider his buffs.  If you are just kitting it really doesn't matter.  Your connection plays more of a part than anything else, besides what drum you have.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
