			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Top 3 stats (and values) for bards on allakhazam.com<a name="42829"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 27 04 10:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm so sad.. only one other person mentioned resists!  Don't ever underestimate the power of resists, especially if you're a pulling bard.  It's not as much of a problem in easy LDoNs / PoP, but if you pull hard ldons or GoD, the last thing you want mid pull is a mob to land a snare/root/1k+ nuke on you.  My previous main had over 200 to all but disease resist unbuffed, and I'm working on the same with my bard.  Even soloing good resists are handy.  I wouldn't recommend mephits in PoN for instance if you haven't got 150+ unbuffed resists.
<br />

<br />
I also believe in HPs and AC quite strongly, with int, mana, and cha pretty close.  My charisma is pretty terrible as far as I'm concerned, which is why I refuse to upgrade the Cloak of Greater Pernicity, and the difference lulling in hard ldon with 280 cha (I haven't bought PP yet) vs lulling with 230 cha is very noticeable.
<br />

<br />
Mana really is less of an issue until you start doing a lot of charming, or until 63 when you get fade; depends on your playstyle.
<br />

<br />
Basically, because bards are such a 'jack-of-all-trades' type of character, until you're reaching the upper level raiding, you're never going to have a 'one suit does all' equipment; you'll need to customise your armour and stats to suit your primary play style.  All the suggestions above have merit depending on the path they've chosen to work towards, be it pulling, soloing, grouping, CC, etc</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=932854>Manitae </a> - 65 Bard, 
E'Ci</span></td>
